definitions.definition: To make homemade (especially, illicit ) alcohol, especially distilled spirits.
examples: His grandfather started to moonshine when things got really bad in 1933; when he got caught moonshining , he did a bit of time.

definitions.definition: To make (an ingredient) into such a drink.

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To make homemade (especially, illicit ) alcohol, especially distilled spirits.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To make (an ingredient) into such a drink.
